# Satirical Copy Guidelines

Corporate Ladder humor = workplace satire, not generic game fluff.

## Tone

- Deadpan corporate jargon ("synergy", "paradigm", "reorg")
- Absurd HR/bureaucracy scenarios
- Self-aware misery, not mean-spirited
- Short punchy lines over long paragraphs

## Terminology

| Context | Use |
|---------|-----|
| UI / HUD | **Energy**, **Deadline** (not "Burnout meter/cloud") |
| API `termination_cause` | Human strings e.g. `"Deadline Crash"`, `"Meeting Collision"` |
| Code obstacle type | `burnout` (engine ID — do not rename without migration plan) |

## Examples (good)

- "Promoted to Manager. Your desktop calendar is destroyed."
- "Attended 214 meetings. No decisions made."
- "Missed the deadline while compiling a budget sheet nobody opened."

## Examples (avoid)

- Generic "Game Over!" without context
- Breaking fourth wall about being a game
- Offensive stereotypes about real companies/people
- HUD label "Burnout" (use Energy / Deadline)

## Where Copy Lives

- **`apps/mini-app/src/game/constants.ts`** — primary source: `FAILURE_REASONS`, `FAILURE_BY_RANK`, `PROMOTION_DIALOGUES`, retry tips, termination labels
- Game over / promotion UI strings in `template.ts` / `app.ts`
- Bot welcome message in `apps/bot/main.py`
- Historical tone reference: [primal.txt](../../primal.txt) (concept v0.1 — not current HUD labels)
